  <namespace name="Rubicon.Web.UI">
    The <b>Rubicon.Web.UI</b> namespace provides classes related the <see cref="System.Web.UI.Page"/> and 
    generic user interface features.
    
    <h3 class="dtH3">Web Accessibility Initiative (WAI)</h3>
    <para>
      The <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/intro/wcag.php" target="_blank">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines</a> 
      defined by the <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI" target="_blank">WAI</a> include a 
      <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG10/full-checklist.html" target="_blank">list of checkpoints</a> that must be 
      met by a web page claiming WAI conformity. These checkpoints have on of three priority levels assigned. 
    </para><para>
      The WAI conformance of a web page is meassured by its conformence level:
    </para>
    <div class="tablediv"> 
    <table class="dtTABLE" cellspacing="0">
      <colgroup>
        <col width="25%"/>
        <col width="75%"/>
      </colgroup>
      <thead>
        <tr valign="top">
          <th>Conformance Level</th>
          <th>Requirement</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Conformance Level "A"</td>
          <td>All Priority 1 checkpoints are satisfied.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Conformance Level "Double-A"</td>
          <td>All Priority 1 and 2 checkpoints are satisfied.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Conformance Level "Triple-A"</td>
          <td>All Priority 1, 2, and 3 checkpoints are satisfied.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    </div>
    <para>
      A web application implemented with the use of the rubicon web controls can enforce WAI conformance.
      This feature is activated by setting the 
      <see cref="T:Rubicon.Web.Configuration.WebConfiguration.WAI">Rubicon.Web.Configuration.WebConfiguration.WAI</see>
      entry in the configuration file.
    </para>
    <para>
      A list of WAI conform controls can be found in the 
      <see href="Rubicon.Web.UI.Controls.html">Rubicon.Web.UI.Controls</see> and
      <see href="Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls.html">Rubicon.ObjectBinding.Web.Controls</see> namespace 
      documentation.
    </para>
  </namespace>

